14/07/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) arrested war crimes suspect Srpko Pustivuk, 47, on Tuesday (July 13th) in Bijelina. He allegedly participated in attacks against civilians in the village of Gornja Bioca, as well as illegal detentions of Bosniaks in 1992. (RTRS, Srna, Tanjug, B92 - 13/07/10)
